#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:5
msgid "Completing Essay Assignments"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:7
msgid "In some courses, you are asked to write essays in response to topics or to questions that do not have simple answers. These essay assignments are called open response assessments (ORA) because they have a flexible design, and can include various assessment options, including peer assessments and self assessments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:13
msgid "In some assignments, you can also submit an image or other type of file. For information about uploading images or other files in your open response assessment, see :ref:`Submit a File with Your Response`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:19
msgid "If you want to try an example open response assessment problem, check out the edX demonstration course, `edX Demo course`_. In addition to giving you a tour of a typical edX course, the edX Demo course contains `information about open response assessments`_ and an `example peer assessment`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:24
msgid "This section describes how to work with open response assessments in your edX course."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:36
msgid "The Steps in an Open Response Assessment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:38
msgid "Open response assessments can have several possible steps, which appear in the order that you must complete them. Future steps are not available until you complete your current step. This topic describes all of the possible steps. The actual steps in your assignment depend on how your course team has designed the assignment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:None
msgid "An example open response assessment, showing a training step, peer\n"
"assessment step and self assessment step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:49
msgid ":ref:`Your Response<Submit Your Response>`. In this first step in an open response assessment, you submit your response to the assignment question."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:52
msgid ":ref:`Learn to Assess Responses<Learn to Assess Responses>`. In this step you practice grading some responses. You evaluate example responses and then see how the grade you gave differs from the grade that a member of the course team gave. The goal is to learn how to assess responses similar to the way that course staff would assess them, using the same rubric."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:59
msgid ":ref:`Assess Peers<Assess Peer Responses>`. You grade responses that other learners in the course have submitted, and other learners in the course grade your responses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:63
msgid "Your course team decides the number of peer assessments that you have to perform and receive. For example, you might be required to assess the responses of two of your peers, as well as receive assessments by two of your peers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:68
msgid ":ref:`Assess Your Response<Assess Your Response>`. In this step you assess your own response, using the same rubric that you used to perform peer assessments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:72
msgid ":ref:`Staff Grade <Staff Grade>`. Members of the course team assess your response. If you receive a staff grade for your assignment, it always overrides any peer assessment grades that you receive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:76
msgid "Course staff can grade your open response assignment even if a staff assessment step is not included in the assignment. This might happen if, for example, you receive peer assessments of your response that are inappropriate. In such cases, course staff can perform an assessment of your response that overrides any peer assessment grades."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:87
msgid "How Grading Is Done In Open Response Assessments"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:89
msgid "Grading for every type of assessment in an ORA assignment is done by comparing each response against the same set of guidelines, called a rubric. Every open response assessment has a rubric provided by the course team."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:93
msgid "A rubric consists of several criteria and a set of options for each criterion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:95
msgid "The parts of the rubric in the image below are labelled as follows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:97
msgid "**Criteria**. Each criterion describes characteristics that a response should have, such as concepts that a response should cover, or the amount of supporting information that a response must include."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:101
msgid "**Options**. Each criterion has options which describe how well each response satisfies the criterion. The options are usually a range of ratings, for example \"Fair\", \"Good\", or \"Excellent\", with details to help you decide the rating."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:106
msgid "When you assess a response, you evaluate the response, and for each criterion, select the option that best describes how well the response met that criterion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:None
msgid "An example rubric showing criteria and options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:119
msgid "Completing an Open Response Assessment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:121
msgid "An open response assessment's steps are arranged in the order that you must complete them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:124
msgid "The topics in this section describe how you complete an example open response assessment that includes a response step, an assessment training step, a peer assessment step, a self assessment step, and a staff grade step. Your actual assignment might not contain all of these steps. Possible steps are described in :ref:`Steps in an Open Response Assessment`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:134
msgid "At any time during an assessment, you can see your progress at the bottom of the page under **Your Grade**. A message indicates the steps that must still be completed before you can receive your final grade for the assignment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:143
msgid "Submit Your Response"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:145
msgid "To submit your response to an open response assessment question, follow these steps."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:148
msgid "Read each question carefully. Some course teams include important information in the question, such as how long a response must be, or specific topics that your response must cover."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:154
msgid "The total word count for your response cannot be more than 10,000 words (approximately the equivalent of 20 pages of 8.5x11 inch paper, with single-spaced text)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:158
msgid "For each question, enter your response into the field under **Your Response**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:163
msgid "In some assignments, you can submit images or other types of files along with or instead of a written response. If you can upload files in your assignment, **Browse** and **Upload your files** options are available below the response field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:168
msgid "For information about uploading images or other files in your ORA assignment, see :ref:`Submit a File with Your Response`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:173
msgid "For assignments that require LaTeX responses, a **Preview in LaTeX** option is available that you can use to preview your work before you submit your response."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:177
msgid "When you have finished answering all of the questions, select **Submit your response and move to the next step**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:180
msgid "If you need more time, you can select **Save Your Progress** to save a draft of your responses, and then come back and submit them later."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:None
msgid "A response in progress in an ORA assignment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:188
msgid "After you submit your response, the next step, which is usually either assessment training or peer assessment, becomes available. However, you do not have to start the next step right away. If you want to stop working and come back later, just refresh or reopen your browser when you come back."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:197
msgid "Submit a File with Your Response"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:199
msgid "If your assignment requires or allows you to submit images or other types of files, you see two buttons below the response field: **Choose Files** one one side of the page, and **Upload Files** on the other side of the page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:205
msgid "The cumulative size of the files that you upload must be less than 500 MB."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:207
msgid "Image files can be in .jpg, .gif, or .png format."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:209
msgid "To upload files in your response, follow these steps."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:211
msgid "Below the response field, select **Choose Files**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:213
msgid "In the dialog box that opens, select the file that you want to upload, and then select **Open**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:216
msgid "A preview image of each file is visible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:218
msgid "In the boxes next to each preview image, enter a written description of the image. This step is required to help learners who cannot see or access the image understand and evaluate your response."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:222
msgid "Across from the **Choose Files** button, select **Upload files**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:224
msgid "You can replace the files that you uploaded with different files until you submit your response. To replace your uploaded files, repeat steps 1-3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:229
msgid "View Your Submitted Response"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:231
msgid "You can view your own response at any time after you submit it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:233
msgid "Select the **Your Response** heading in the assignment to expand the section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:235
msgid "Your response appears, along with the status of the response, and information about additional steps you have to complete before you receive your grade."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:244
msgid "Learn to Assess Responses"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:246
msgid "Some ORA assignments include a training step so that you can learn how to effectively assess responses for a later peer assessment step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:249
msgid "In a training step, you evaluate example responses using a provided rubric as a guide for grading. After you complete the grading, you are shown how the grades you gave differ from the grades that a member of the course team gave. The goal is to learn how to assess responses similar to the way that course staff would assess them, using the same :ref:`rubric<How Grading Is Done in ORA>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:256
msgid "Complete the training step as follows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:258
msgid "Read each sample response and the rubric carefully, then for each criterion, select the option that you think best reflect the response."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:261
msgid "When you are satisfied with your assessment, select **Compare your selections with the instructor's selections**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:264
msgid "If all of your selections are the same as the instructor's selections, the next sample response opens automatically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:267
msgid "If any option that you select is not the same as the instructor's selection, you see the response again, with a message indicating that your assessment differs from the instructor's assessment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:271
msgid "If your assessment did not match the instructor's assessment, review the response again and consider why the instructor assessed the response differently than you did. Continue to assess the example response until the options you select for all criteria match options selected by the instructor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:None
msgid "Example training step with one grade that matched and another grade\n"
"that did not match the grade that the course team gave."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:282
msgid "When you have successfully assessed the sample responses, the next step in the assignment becomes available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:290
msgid "Assess Peer Responses"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:292
msgid "In the peer assessment step of an open response assessment, you perform assessments of responses that were submitted by other learners in your course. The course team sets the requirement for how many peer assessments each learner is expected to complete."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:297
msgid "At the top of the peer assessment step, you can see counts of how many responses you are expected to assess and how many you have already assessed. For example, if you are required to perform 3 peer assessments and are about to start your first peer assessment, the count appears as \"1 of 3\". Within the **Assess Peers** step, you see each question, a learner's response, and the rubric that you will use to grade the response."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:None
msgid "An in-progress peer assessment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:308
msgid "You assess other learners' responses by selecting options in the rubric. This process will be familiar to you if your assignment included the :ref:`learn to assess responses<Learn to Assess Responses>` step. Additionally, this step has a field below the rubric where you can provide comments about the learner's response."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:314
msgid "In addition to a field for overall comments on a learner's response, some peer assessments include **Comments** fields for individual criteria that allow you to enter up to 300 characters. In some assessments, you must enter comments before you can submit the assessment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:319
msgid "After you have selected options in the rubric and provided comments about the response, select **Submit your assessment and move to response #{number}**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:322
msgid "After you submit each peer assessment, a response from another learner becomes available, until you have assessed the required number of responses. The count of how many responses you have assessed updates after you assess each response."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:327
msgid "When you have completed the required number of peer assessments, the next step in the assignment becomes available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:330
msgid "If there are no submitted responses available for grading, a status message indicates that no peer responses are currently available for you to assess, and that you should check back later."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:337
msgid "Assess Additional Peer Responses (optional)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:339
msgid "If you have assessed the required number of peer responses, the peer assessment step collapses so that only the **Assess Peers** heading is visible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:343
msgid "If you want to, you can assess more peer responses than the assignment requires. To assess more responses, select the **Assess Peers** heading to expand the step, and then select **Continue Assessing Peers**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:352
msgid "Assess Your Response"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:354
msgid "When you have completed the required number of peer assessments, the self assessment step of the assignment becomes available. You see your response along with the same rubric that you used in the peer assessment step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:358
msgid "Perform an assessment of your own response, and then select **Submit Your Assessment**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:361
msgid "When you have completed assessing your own response, the next step in the assignment becomes available. If there are no further steps, and if you have received the required number of peer assessments on your own response, you can :ref:`receive your score<Receive Your Score and Provide Feedback>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:371
msgid "Staff Grade"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:373
msgid "In some assignments, a staff assessment step is included for a member of the course team to grade your responses. You do not need to take any action for this step. The status of the **Staff Grade** step changes to **Complete** when a member of the course team has completed grading your response."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:378
msgid "If a **Staff Grade** step exists in your assignment, you receive your final assignment grade when staff grading is complete, even if your response has not been assessed by the required number of peer reviewers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:382
msgid "Course staff can grade your open response assignment even if a staff assessment step is not included in the assignment. This might happen if, for example, you receive peer assessments of your response that are inappropriate. In such cases, course staff can perform an assessment of your response that overrides any peer assessment grades. If a member of the course staff has graded your response, a **Staff Grade** section appears in the grading details for your assignment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:395
msgid "Receive Your Score and Provide Feedback"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:397
msgid "You receive your score for an open response assessment when you have completed the following steps."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:400
msgid ":ref:`Submitted your response<Submit Your Response>` to the question."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:401
msgid "Completed the :ref:`assessment training step<Learn to Assess Responses>` (if included)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:403
msgid "Performed the required number of :ref:`peer assessments<Assess Peer Responses>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:405
msgid "Performed a :ref:`self assessment<Assess Your Response>` (if included)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:406
msgid "Received the required number of peer assessments of your own work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:407
msgid "Received a :ref:`staff assessment<Staff Grade>` (if included)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:409
msgid "If other learners are still assessing your response, you see the following message below the **Assess Your Response** step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:420
msgid "If you see this message, check back periodically until peer assessments of your work are complete."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:428
msgid "View Your Score"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:430
msgid "When peer assessment is complete, and if the assignment does not include a staff assessment step, you can see the scores you received from all of the peers who scored your work, as well as your self assessment. You can also see any comments that your peers have provided."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:None
msgid "The \"Your Grade\" section of an ORA assignment shows the total grade\n"
"as well as a breakdown by criterion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:440
msgid "If the assignment included a staff assessment step, you receive your final grade when a member of the course team has graded your response. If a staff assessment step is included in the assignment, peer assessment grades and comments are included in the assignment grade details, but the staff grade becomes the final grade."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:451
msgid "Provide Feedback on Peer Assessments Received"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:453
msgid "If you want to, you can provide feedback on the peer scores that you received, under **Provide Feedback on Peer Assessments**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:None
msgid "In the \"Provide feedback on peer assessments\" section, you can select\n"
"statements or written comments as feedback on the peer scores that you\n"
"received."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:467
msgid "View Top Responses (optional)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:469
msgid "Some open response assessments include a **Top Responses** section below your own score, that shows the highest scoring responses that were submitted for each question."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:473
msgid "If your course team included this section in your assignment, it appears only after you have completed all the steps of the assignment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:None
msgid "Section that shows the text and scores of the top three responses for\n"
"the assignment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:486
msgid "How Peer Assessment Scores Are Calculated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:488
msgid "If a :ref:`staff grade<Staff Grade>` is provided in the assignment, either because a staff assessment step was included or because a member of the course team graded your response to override inappropriate peer assessments, peer assessments are not taken into account in the grading. If a staff grade exists, it is always your final grade."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:494
msgid "Peer assessments are scored by criteria. Each criterion's score is the median, not the average, of the scores that each peer assessor gave that criterion. For example, if the Ideas criterion in a peer assessment receives 10 from one learner, 9 from a second learner, and 5 from a third learner, the score for that criterion is 9 (the median), not 8 (the average)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/SFD_ORA.rst:500
msgid "Your final score for a peer assessment is the sum of the median scores for each individual criterion."
msgstr ""

